Argentine Stocks: Banco Macro and Grupo Financiero Galicia Rise

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-03-30T21:08:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/argentine-stocks-banco-macro-and-grupo-financiero-galicia-rise.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4:01 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index rose 1.6 percent to 3,376.44.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)   rose 3 percent to 17.10 pesos, the
steepest increase in four weeks.  Argentina ’s largest lender by
market value expects 40 percent expansion in its loan portfolio
in 2011, Chairman Jorge Brito said at a conference, Reuters
reported.  Grupo Financiero Galicia SA (GGAL)  , the country’s
largest consumer lender, increased 2.5 percent to 5.36 pesos,
the biggest jump in more than nine weeks. Argentine sovereign
bond prices rose today, which signals higher value for banks’
fixed income holdings.  YPF SA (YPFD)   rose 1.4 percent to 184 pesos. The unit of
Repsol YPF SA,  Spain ’s largest oil company, has increased 3.4
percent in the last two days, the biggest two-day gain in four
weeks, after the Argentine government announced yesterday it had
suspended a gasoline price freeze imposed in February.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
